DoT,heal,Nuke is very common as a druid.<br><br><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />The timer really wont be any restriction at all. Not in comparison to what is gained. It *only* limits you if you need to change stance twice in a 5 minutes period of time. Exactly how often is that going to happen?<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Usually every few mobs to be honest.<br>We may not heal someone every other mob but my finger sits right on that heal button more often than not on almost every pull. Before the mob is slowed or if slow is resisted a second or two slip up by the cleric can kill the tank.<br><br>Edit: Almost forgot. The 25% increase is rumored to effect nukes only. So this won't help much as a druids main DPS comes from our DoT's. Not our nukes.<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 17 21:44:37 2005 by jchapin</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />A good player will make a bad character look good.<br>A good character will NOT make a bad player look good. </td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
