o I'm not in a position to talk about it yet, currently my DPS is on a par with the other DPS classes I play with. Based on this I suspect the DPS at higher levels is an itemisation problem rather than a skill or mechanics issue, but I may be wrong.<br><br>But better pulling for Rangers is an issue that could be of benefit to every one in the game.<br><br>In the higher level zones, GoD and OoW in particular, pulling has become much more dificult. Now, there is nothing wrong with that, I think it is to be expected that things will be harder to do in zones of this level, but the balance has changed so much that without a FD puller or a Bard, you have very limited options for your group. Yes I know that in some areas Rangers and Druids can manage, Enchanters can as well, but I think everyone that plays in these places would agree, the risks and downtime are significantly increased when you have to make do with a non FD or Bard puller.<br><br>As things are now, the Bards, Monks and SKs in our guild are the first choice pick for any one forming a group and then everyone else either tries to crowd into the &quot;easy&quot; spots, goes kiting at the PoF tables or does trade skills (or logs off). Another class that is a viable puller would mean more grouping and playing time for everyone. And Rangers are a prime candidate for this I believe.<br><br>Properly AAed and equipped a Ranger's defenses and AC are not too terrible, it wouldn't take too much tweaking to get them to a level where they can survive a few hits during the hand over to the tank. All they need is a viable all zone splitting tool.<br><br>If this is to be a true &quot;class re-envisioning&quot; and not just some more tinkering at the edges, then why not bring in a new ability all together?<br><br>One like this, that gives many more groups the opportunity to go to places like Vxed or MPG for example, that is currently out of bounds for 75% of the player population?</p><br /><span class="sm">-------